d style guide protects that consistency as your team grows and you work with external designers, printers and partners."},{"q":"Can I download this Brand Style Guide as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Brand Style Guide suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'brand-style-guide-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"organization_name","label":"Your Organization / Event","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"proposal_title","label":"Proposal Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Sponsorship Proposal"},{"name":"proposal_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"sponsor","label":"Prepared For (Prospective Sponsor)","type":"party","required":true},{"name":"opportunity_overview","label":"Opportunity Overview","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"This proposal invites your organisation to partner with us as a sponsor. It describes the opportunity, the audience you will reach, the benefits to your brand, and the sponsorship packages available."},{"name":"audience_reach","label":"Audience & Reach","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Describe the audience the sponsor will reach — size, demographics, channels and engagement — with evidence where possible."},{"name":"packages","label":"Sponsorship Packages & Benefits","type":"line_items","required":true,"has_unit":true},{"name":"currency","label":"Currency","type":"text","required":false,"default":"USD"},{"name":"activation","label":"Activation & Deliverables","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Explain how the sponsorship will be activated and the specific deliverables and visibility the sponsor will receive."},{"name":"response_by","label":"Please Respond By","type":"date","required":false},{"name":"contact","label":"Contact (Name, Email, Phone)","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"prepared_signature","label":"Authorized Signature","type":"signature","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What makes a compelling sponsorship proposal?","a":"A compelling proposal sells the value to the sponsor, not just your need for funds: it quantifies the audience and reach, spells out the brand benefits and activation, offers clear tiered packages with pricing, and makes it easy to say yes. Lead with what the sponsor gains and back it with evidence."},{"q":"How should sponsorship packages be structured?","a":"Offer a small number of clearly differentiated tiers (for example bronze, silver, gold) with escalating visibility and benefits and transparent pricing. Tiered packages let sponsors self-select at the level that fits their budget and goals, and increase the average value of deals."},{"q":"Can I download this Sponsorship Proposal as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Sponsorship Proposal suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'sponsorship-proposal-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"brand_name","label":"Brand / Company","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"campaign_name","label":"Campaign Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"brief_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"objective","label":"Campaign Objective","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"State the single primary objective of this campaign (for example nurture leads, drive sales, re-engage, announce) and the metric that defines success."},{"name":"target_audience","label":"Target Audience / Segment","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Define the list segment(s) this campaign targets and why."},{"name":"send_dates","label":"Send Date(s) / Schedule","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"subject_line","label":"Subject Line(s)","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"key_message","label":"Key Message & Offer","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Describe the core message, the value proposition and any offer or incentive."},{"name":"call_to_action","label":"Primary Call to Action","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"content_outline","label":"Content Outline","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Outline the email structure — hook, body, proof, CTA — and any assets required."},{"name":"kpis","label":"Success Metrics (KPIs)","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Define the KPIs (open rate, click rate, conversions, revenue) and targets used to judge the campaign."},{"name":"prepared_by","label":"Prepared By","type":"text","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What should an email campaign brief include?","a":"A focused email brief defines a single objective and success metric, the target segment, the key message and offer, the subject line and primary call to action, the schedule, and the KPIs. Aligning everyone on one objective before writing produces sharper, higher-converting campaigns."},{"q":"How do I improve email open and click rates?","a":"Segment your list so the message is relevant, write a clear benefit-led subject line, keep one primary call to action, and personalise where you can. Define your target open/click/conversion rates in the brief and test subject lines and send times to improve over time — while respecting consent and unsubscribe rules under laws like GDPR and CAN-SPAM."},{"q":"Can I download this Email Marketing Campaign Brief as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Email Marketing Campaign Brief suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'email-marketing-campaign-brief-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"organization_name","label":"Organization","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"report_title","label":"Report Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Market Research Report"},{"name":"report_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"prepared_by","label":"Prepared By","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"executive_summary","label":"Executive Summary","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"This report summarises the research objectives, methodology, key findings and recommendations for the market or question studied."},{"name":"objectives_methodology","label":"Objectives & Methodology","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"State the research objectives and describe the methodology — sources, sample, methods and any limitations — so the findings can be judged on their merits."},{"name":"key_findings","label":"Key Findings","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"market_analysis","label":"Market Analysis & Insights","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Analyse the findings: market size and trends, customer needs and behaviour, and the competitive landscape."},{"name":"recommendations","label":"Recommendations","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Set out clear, actionable recommendations that follow from the findings, with their expected impact."},{"name":"approved_by","label":"Approved By","type":"text","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What should a market research report contain?","a":"A credible research report states the objectives and methodology (so readers can judge reliability), presents the key findings with evidence, analyses what they mean for the market and customers, and ends with clear, actionable recommendations. Transparency about method and limitations is what makes the conclusions trustworthy."},{"q":"Why document the research methodology?","a":"Documenting the sources, sample and methods lets decision-makers weigh how much confidence to place in the findings and allows the research to be repeated or built upon. Hiding the method undermines credibility; stating it — including limitations — strengthens it."},{"q":"Can I download this Market Research Report as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Market Research Report suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'market-research-report-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"organization_name","label":"Organization","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"event_name","label":"Event Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"event_type","label":"Event Type","type":"select","required":false,"options":["Conference","Webinar","Product Launch","Trade Show","Workshop","Networking","Other"],"default":"Conference"},{"name":"event_date","label":"Event Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"venue","label":"Venue / Platform","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"objectives","label":"Objectives & Target Audience","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"State what the event aims to achieve (awareness, leads, sales, community) and who it is for."},{"name":"promotion_strategy","label":"Promotion Strategy","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Describe how you will promote the event across channels (email, social, paid, partners, PR) and the timeline of activity."},{"name":"budget","label":"Budget & Logistics","type":"line_items","required":true,"has_unit":true},{"name":"currency","label":"Currency","type":"text","required":false,"default":"USD"},{"name":"run_of_show","label":"Run of Show / Agenda","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Outline the event programme and key timings."},{"name":"success_metrics","label":"Success Metrics","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Define how success will be measured (registrations, attendance, leads, engagement, ROI)."},{"name":"prepared_by","label":"Prepared By","type":"text","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What should an event marketing plan cover?","a":"A complete event plan covers the objectives and audience, the promotion strategy and timeline across channels, the budget and logistics, the run of show, and the metrics used to judge success. Tying promotion and spend to clear objectives and KPIs is what turns an event into measurable marketing ROI."},{"q":"How far in advance should I promote an event?","a":"It depends on scale, but begin promotion several weeks to a few months ahead for larger events, with a build-up of reminders as the date approaches. Map the promotion timeline in the plan so no channel or reminder is missed and registrations build steadily."},{"q":"Can I download this Event Marketing Plan as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Event Marketing Plan suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'event-marketing-plan-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Your Company","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"case_study_title","label":"Case Study Title","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"client_name","label":"Client / Subject","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"industry","label":"Industry","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"publish_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":false},{"name":"challenge","label":"The Challenge","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Describe the client''s situation and the specific challenge or goal they faced before working with you."},{"name":"solution","label":"The Solution","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Explain what you did — your approach, the work delivered and why it suited the challenge."},{"name":"results","label":"The Results","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Present the outcomes, quantified wherever possible (metrics, percentages, time or cost saved), to demonstrate real impact."},{"name":"testimonial","label":"Client Testimonial","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Include a short, authentic quote from the client describing their experience and the results."},{"name":"call_to_action","label":"Call to Action","type":"text","required":false,"default":"Encourage the reader to take the next step (e.g. get in touch, book a demo)."}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What is the best structure for a marketing case study?","a":"The proven structure is Challenge → Solution → Results: describe the client''s problem, explain what you did, and prove the impact with quantified results, reinforced by a genuine client testimonial and a call to action. Specific numbers and a real customer voice make a case study persuasive."},{"q":"How do I make a case study credible?","a":"Use a real, named client where possible, quantify the results with concrete metrics, and include a direct testimonial. Specificity builds trust — ''38% more qualified leads in three months'' is far more convincing than ''significantly improved results''."},{"q":"Can I download this Case Study as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Case Study suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'case-study-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company / Startup Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"tagline","label":"One-line Pitch","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"outline_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":false},{"name":"problem","label":"Problem","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Describe the real, painful problem your startup solves and who suffers from it."},{"name":"solution","label":"Solution","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Explain your solution and why it is compelling and better than the alternatives."},{"name":"market","label":"Market Opportunity","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Size the market (TAM/SAM/SOM) and the trends that make now the right time."},{"name":"product","label":"Product","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Describe the product, its current stage and what makes it defensible."},{"name":"business_model","label":"Business Model","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Explain how you make money — pricing, unit economics and channels."},{"name":"traction","label":"Traction","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Show evidence of momentum — users, revenue, growth, partnerships or pipeline."},{"name":"competition","label":"Competition","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Map the competitive landscape and your differentiation."},{"name":"team","label":"Team","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Introduce the founders and key team and why you are the right people to win."},{"name":"ask","label":"The Ask","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"State how much you are raising, on what terms, and how you will use the funds to hit the next milestones."}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What slides does an investor pitch deck need?","a":"A standard investor deck covers: problem, solution, market opportunity, product, business model, traction, competition, team, and the ask (how much you''re raising and use of funds). This outline gives you each section so you can tell a clear, compelling story in around 10–12 slides."},{"q":"What do investors look for most in a pitch?","a":"Investors look for a large problem, a compelling and defensible solution, evidence of traction, attractive unit economics, and a team that can execute. Clarity and proof beat hype — quantify the market and your traction, and be specific about how the raise drives the next milestones."},{"q":"Can I download this Pitch Deck Outline as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Pitch Deck Outline suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'pitch-deck-outline-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company / Startup","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"canvas_title","label":"Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Business Model Canvas"},{"name":"canvas_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":false},{"name":"value_propositions","label":"Value Propositions","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"What core value do you deliver to customers, and which problem do you solve or need do you satisfy?"},{"name":"customer_segments","label":"Customer Segments","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Who are your most important customers and segments?"},{"name":"channels","label":"Channels","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"How do you reach and deliver to customers (marketing, sales and distribution channels)?"},{"name":"customer_relationships","label":"Customer Relationships","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"What type of relationship does each segment expect (self-service, personal, community, automated)?"},{"name":"revenue_streams","label":"Revenue Streams","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"How and for what do customers pay, and what is the pricing model?"},{"name":"key_resources","label":"Key Resources","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"What key assets (people, technology, IP, capital) does your model require?"},{"name":"key_activities","label":"Key Activities","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"What key activities must you perform well to deliver your value proposition?"},{"name":"key_partnerships","label":"Key Partnerships","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Who are your key partners and suppliers, and what do they provide?"},{"name":"cost_structure","label":"Cost Structure","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"What are the most important costs in your model, and which are fixed or variable?"}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What is the Business Model Canvas?","a":"The Business Model Canvas is an internationally used one-page framework that maps the nine building blocks of a business: value propositions, customer segments, channels, customer relationships, revenue streams, key resources, key activities, key partnerships and cost structure. It gives founders and teams a shared, at-a-glance view of how the business creates, delivers and captures value."},{"q":"Why use a canvas instead of a long business plan?","a":"A canvas is fast to create, easy to iterate, and forces clarity on the essentials and how they fit together. It is ideal for early-stage exploration and pivots; you can develop a detailed business plan once the model is validated."},{"q":"Can I download this Business Model Canvas as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Business Model Canvas suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'business-model-canvas-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"document_title","label":"Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Term Sheet"},{"name":"term_sheet_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"investor","label":"Investor","type":"party","required":true},{"name":"company","label":"Company","type":"party","required":true},{"name":"investment_amount","label":"Investment Amount","type":"number","required":true},{"name":"currency","label":"Currency","type":"text","required":false,"default":"USD"},{"name":"instrument","label":"Instrument","type":"text","required":false,"default":"Preferred Equity / SAFE / Convertible Note"},{"name":"pre_money_valuation","label":"Pre-Money Valuation","type":"number","required":false},{"name":"equity_percentage","label":"Equity / Ownership","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"key_terms","label":"Key Terms","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Set out the principal economic and control terms — valuation, option pool, liquidation preference, anti-dilution, board composition, voting and protective provisions, and information rights — as the basis for definitive documents."},{"name":"conditions","label":"Conditions & Exclusivity","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Describe conditions to closing (due diligence, legal documentation, approvals) and any exclusivity/no-shop period."},{"name":"binding_clause","label":"Binding / Non-Binding","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Except for the confidentiality, exclusivity and governing-law provisions, this term sheet is a non-binding expression of intent and does not create a legally binding obligation to invest, which arises only on signing definitive agreements."},{"name":"governing_law","label":"Governing Law / Jurisdiction","type":"text","required":false,"default":"This document shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the applicable jurisdiction stated by the parties."},{"name":"investor_signature","label":"Investor Signature","type":"signature","required":false},{"name":"company_signature","label":"Company Signature","type":"signature","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"Is a term sheet legally binding?","a":"Most term sheets are largely non-binding — they record the key terms the parties intend to put into definitive agreements — except for specific provisions that are usually binding, such as confidentiality, exclusivity/no-shop and governing law. The template makes this binding/non-binding split explicit, which is standard international practice."},{"q":"What key terms does a venture term sheet cover?","a":"Typical terms include the investment amount and instrument, pre-money valuation and resulting ownership, the option pool, liquidation preference, anti-dilution protection, board composition, voting and protective provisions, and information rights. These shape the economics and control of the deal, so review them with experienced counsel before signing."},{"q":"Can I download this Investment Term Sheet as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Investment Term Sheet suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'term-sheet-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"table_title","label":"Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Capitalization Table"},{"name":"as_of_date","label":"As of Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"currency","label":"Currency","type":"text","required":false,"default":"USD"},{"name":"total_shares","label":"Total Shares Issued","type":"number","required":false},{"name":"shareholders","label":"Shareholders & Holdings","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"option_pool","label":"Option Pool / Convertibles","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"notes","label":"Notes","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"This capitalization table summarises the ownership of the company as of the date stated, including issued shares, the option pool and any convertible instruments. Percentages are calculated on the basis indicated (issued or fully diluted)."},{"name":"prepared_by","label":"Prepared By","type":"text","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What is a cap table and why does it matter?","a":"A capitalization (cap) table records who owns what in a company — founders, investors, and the option pool — with share counts and ownership percentages. It is essential for fundraising, option grants and exits, and investors will scrutinise it, so keeping it accurate and up to date is critical from day one."},{"q":"What is the difference between issued and fully diluted ownership?","a":"Issued ownership is based on shares actually issued today; fully diluted ownership also counts options, warrants and convertible instruments as if exercised or converted. Investors usually negotiate on a fully diluted basis, so state clearly which basis your percentages use."},{"q":"Can I download this Capitalization Table as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Capitalization Table suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'cap-table-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"update_period","label":"Update Period (e.g. Month/Quarter)","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"update_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"highlights","label":"Highlights & Lowlights","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Open with the key wins and the key challenges since the last update — investors value candour about both."},{"name":"key_metrics","label":"Key Metrics (KPI / This Period / Change)","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"financials","label":"Financial Summary","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Summarise revenue, burn, cash on hand and runway so investors can see the financial picture at a glance."},{"name":"progress","label":"Product & Team Progress","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Describe progress on product, customers, hiring and partnerships since the last update."},{"name":"asks","label":"Asks / How You Can Help","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Tell investors specifically how they can help — intros, hiring, advice — investors are a resource, not just a reporting line."},{"name":"prepared_by","label":"Prepared By","type":"text","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What should a regular investor update include?","a":"A good investor update shares highlights and lowlights, the key metrics with their change, a financial summary (revenue, burn, cash and runway), progress on product and team, and specific asks. Regular, candid updates build trust, keep investors engaged, and make it easier to raise your next round."},{"q":"How often should startups send investor updates?","a":"Monthly or quarterly is typical. Consistency matters more than frequency — pick a cadence you can sustain, be honest about challenges as well as wins, and always include clear asks so investors can actively help."},{"q":"Can I download this Investor Update as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Investor Update suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'investor-update-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"document_title","label":"Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Executive Summary"},{"name":"summary_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":false},{"name":"overview","label":"Company Overview","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Introduce the company in a sentence or two — what you do, for whom, and why it matters."},{"name":"problem_solution","label":"Problem & Solution","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"State the problem you solve and your solution, clearly and concisely."},{"name":"market","label":"Market Opportunity","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Summarise the market size and opportunity."},{"name":"business_model","label":"Business Model","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Explain briefly how the business makes money."},{"name":"traction","label":"Traction & Milestones","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Highlight key achievements and momentum to date."},{"name":"team","label":"Team","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Introduce the key people and why they can execute."},{"name":"financials_ask","label":"Financials & Ask","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Summarise the financial highlights or projections and, if raising, the funding ask and use of funds."},{"name":"prepared_by","label":"Prepared By","type":"text","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What is an executive summary and why is it important?","a":"An executive summary is a concise, standalone overview of a business or plan — covering the company, problem and solution, market, model, traction, team and financial ask — written so a busy reader can grasp the essentials in a minute. It is often the only part investors or partners read first, so it must earn the deeper read."},{"q":"How long should an executive summary be?","a":"Keep it to one page (or two at most). Lead with the most compelling points, write in plain, confident language, and make sure it stands on its own without the full document. Edit ruthlessly — every sentence should add value."},{"q":"Can I download this Executive Summary as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Executive Summary suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'executive-summary-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"document_title","label":"Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Letter of Intent"},{"name":"loi_date","label":"Date","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"party_a","label":"Party A","type":"party","required":true},{"name":"party_b","label":"Party B","type":"party","required":true},{"name":"purpose","label":"Purpose / Proposed Transaction","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"This Letter of Intent sets out the parties'' mutual intention to proceed with the proposed transaction or relationship described below, and the principal terms on which they intend to negotiate definitive agreements in good faith."},{"name":"key_terms","label":"Principal Terms","type":"textarea","required":true,"default":"Summarise the key proposed terms — scope, price/consideration, structure, timeline and key conditions — as the basis for the definitive agreement."},{"name":"due_diligence","label":"Due Diligence & Conditions","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Describe any due diligence, approvals or conditions that must be satisfied before the parties enter into binding agreements."},{"name":"exclusivity_period","label":"Exclusivity Period","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"binding_clause","label":"Binding / Non-Binding","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Except for the provisions on confidentiality, exclusivity, costs and governing law, this Letter of Intent is a non-binding statement of intent and does not create any binding obligation to complete the transaction, which arises only on signing definitive agreements."},{"name":"governing_law","label":"Governing Law / Jurisdiction","type":"text","required":false,"default":"This document shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the applicable jurisdiction stated by the parties."},{"name":"party_a_signature","label":"Party A Signature","type":"signature","required":false},{"name":"party_b_signature","label":"Party B Signature","type":"signature","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"Is a letter of intent legally binding?","a":"A letter of intent is generally non-binding as to the main transaction — it records the parties'' intention and the principal terms they will negotiate in good faith — while certain clauses (confidentiality, exclusivity, costs, governing law) are usually binding. The template states this split clearly. Careful wording matters, because poorly drafted LOIs can unintentionally create binding obligations."},{"q":"When should I use a letter of intent?","a":"Use an LOI to record serious intent and the headline terms before investing in full due diligence and definitive contracts — common in acquisitions, investments, partnerships and major commercial deals. It aligns the parties and can secure exclusivity while the detailed agreement is negotiated."},{"q":"Can I download this Letter of Intent as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Letter of Intent suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'letter-of-intent-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company / Startup","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"plan_title","label":"Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Startup Budget Plan"},{"name":"budget_period_from","label":"Period From","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"budget_period_to","label":"Period To","type":"date","required":true},{"name":"currency","label":"Currency","type":"text","required":false,"default":"USD"},{"name":"starting_cash","label":"Starting Cash / Funding","type":"number","required":false},{"name":"revenue_projections","label":"Projected Revenue","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"expenses","label":"Projected Expenses","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"assumptions","label":"Key Assumptions","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Document the assumptions behind your revenue and cost projections (growth rate, pricing, headcount, conversion) so the budget can be understood and stress-tested."},{"name":"runway_note","label":"Burn Rate & Runway","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Summarise your monthly net burn and the resulting runway (how many months your cash lasts), and the milestones you aim to reach before needing more funding."},{"name":"prepared_by","label":"Prepared By","type":"text","required":false}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What should a startup budget plan include?","a":"A startup budget plan projects revenue and expenses over a period, states the starting cash, and — crucially — calculates burn rate and runway (how many months the cash lasts). Documenting the assumptions lets you and investors stress-test the numbers and plan the next raise around clear milestones."},{"q":"What is burn rate and runway, and why do they matter?","a":"Burn rate is how much cash your startup spends net each month; runway is how many months your remaining cash will last at that burn. They are the single most important numbers for an early-stage startup — they tell you how long you have to hit the milestones needed for the next round or profitability."},{"q":"Can I download this Startup Budget Plan as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Startup Budget Plan suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'startup-budget-plan-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"full_name","label":"Full Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"headline","label":"Professional Headline","type":"text","required":false,"default":"Results-driven professional"},{"name":"email","label":"Email","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"phone","label":"Phone","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"location","label":"Location","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"linkedin","label":"LinkedIn / Portfolio URL","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"summary","label":"Professional Summary","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"A concise, achievement-focused summary of your experience, key skills and the value you bring, tailored to the role you are applying for."},{"name":"work_experience","label":"Work Experience","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"education","label":"Education","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"skills","label":"Key Skills","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"List your most relevant technical and soft skills, separated by commas."},{"name":"certifications","label":"Certifications & Awards","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"languages","label":"Languages","type":"textarea","required":false},{"name":"references","label":"References","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"Available on request."}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"How do I make my CV stand out to international employers?","a":"Lead with a tailored professional summary, quantify achievements (not just duties), match keywords to the job description, keep formatting clean and consistent, and keep it to one or two pages. This template produces a clean, ATS-friendly layout that works for applications in the US, UK, EU and beyond."},{"q":"What is the difference between a CV and a resume?","a":"In the US a ''resume'' is a concise one-to-two page summary, while a ''CV'' is a longer academic document. In the UK, EU and much of the world ''CV'' simply means the standard job-application document. This generator produces a professional, internationally accepted format for either use."},{"q":"Can I download this CV / Resume as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this CV / Resume suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'cv-resume-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET fields_schema = '{"fields":[{"name":"company_name","label":"Company Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"payslip_title","label":"Title","type":"text","required":true,"default":"Salary Slip"},{"name":"employee_name","label":"Employee Name","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"employee_id","label":"Employee ID","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"designation","label":"Designation","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"department","label":"Department","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"pay_period","label":"Pay Period","type":"text","required":true},{"name":"pay_date","label":"Pay Date","type":"date","required":false},{"name":"currency","label":"Currency","type":"text","required":false,"default":"USD"},{"name":"days_worked","label":"Days / Hours Worked","type":"number","required":false},{"name":"bank_account","label":"Bank Account (last 4 digits)","type":"text","required":false},{"name":"earnings","label":"Earnings","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"deductions","label":"Deductions","type":"line_items","required":true},{"name":"notes","label":"Notes","type":"textarea","required":false,"default":"This payslip is a computer-generated statement of earnings and deductions for the stated pay period. Please retain it for your records."}]}', faqs = '[{"q":"What should a compliant salary slip (payslip) show?","a":"A payslip should show the employer and employee details, the pay period, gross earnings broken down (basic, allowances, overtime), itemised deductions (tax, social security/insurance, pension), and the net pay. In many countries (e.g. the UK and most of the EU) providing an itemised payslip is a legal requirement."},{"q":"Can I show multiple earnings and deduction lines?","a":"Yes. Add a line for each earning (basic salary, allowances, bonuses) and each deduction (income tax, social-security/insurance, loan repayments). The gross, total deductions and net pay are presented clearly for the employee."},{"q":"Can I download this Salary Slip as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Salary Slip suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'salary-slip-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET faqs = '[{"q":"What should a professional company profile include?","a":"A strong company profile presents your company name and branding, an overview and mission, your history and milestones, products and services, your team or leadership, key clients or achievements, and contact details. It is used in proposals, tenders, investor and partner meetings, so a polished, complete profile builds immediate credibility."},{"q":"How is a company profile different from a business plan?","a":"A company profile is an outward-facing introduction to who you are and what you offer, used for marketing and relationships; a business plan is an internal/investor document detailing strategy and financial projections. This generator focuses on a professional, presentation-ready company profile."},{"q":"Can I download this Company Profile as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Company Profile suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'company-profile-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET faqs = '[{"q":"Does this privacy policy help with GDPR and CCPA compliance?","a":"The template is structured around the disclosures expected by major privacy laws including the EU/UK GDPR and the California CCPA/CPRA — what personal data you collect, the purposes and legal basis, sharing, retention, security, and the rights of data subjects. Complete each section accurately for your business and, for regulated or high-risk processing, have it reviewed by a privacy professional."},{"q":"Where should I display my privacy policy?","a":"Publish it at a stable URL linked from your website footer, app stores, sign-up and checkout forms, and anywhere you collect personal data. Many laws and platforms (Apple, Google, ad networks) require an accessible, up-to-date privacy policy."},{"q":"Can I download this Privacy Policy as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Privacy Policy suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'privacy-policy-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET faqs = '[{"q":"Do I legally need a cookie policy and consent banner?","a":"If your website uses cookies or similar technologies and you have visitors in the EU/UK, the ePrivacy rules and GDPR require clear information about cookies and, for non-essential cookies, prior consent. A cookie policy explaining the categories and purposes of cookies is the standard way to meet this transparency obligation."},{"q":"What should a cookie policy explain?","a":"It should describe the types of cookies used (strictly necessary, performance, functional, targeting), their purpose and duration, any third-party cookies, and how users can manage or withdraw consent through their browser or your preferences tool."},{"q":"Can I download this Cookie Policy as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Cookie Policy suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'cookie-policy-generator';
UPDATE document_templates SET faqs = '[{"q":"What makes a refund policy enforceable and fair?","a":"A clear refund policy states what can be returned or refunded, the time window, the condition of goods, who pays return shipping, and how and when refunds are issued. In the EU/UK consumers also have statutory cancellation rights for many distance sales, which your policy should respect as a minimum."},{"q":"Where should I display my refund policy?","a":"Show it before purchase — on product pages, at checkout, and in order confirmations — and link it from your website footer. Clear, accessible refund terms reduce disputes and chargebacks and are required by most payment providers and marketplaces."},{"q":"Can I download this Refund Policy as PDF and Word?","a":"Yes. Every document you create on Invoxaco can be exported as a polished, print-ready PDF, and Pro and Premium plans can also download a fully editable Microsoft Word (DOCX) file."},{"q":"Is this Refund Policy suitable for use in the US, UK, EU and other countries?","a":"The template uses clear, internationally accepted business language and a neutral structure that works across the United States, United Kingdom, European Union and most other jurisdictions. Set the governing law or jurisdiction field to your country, and for high-value or regulated matters have a local professional review the final document."},{"q":"Can I add my company logo, branding and signature?","a":"Yes. Add your logo, brand colour, authorised signature and company stamp once in your settings and they are applied automatically to this and every other document you generate."}]' WHERE slug = 'refund-policy-generator';
